Dynamic Image Slider
Welcome to the Dynamic Image Slider project! This project is a React-based image slider that enhances user experience by providing a visually appealing and interactive way to display images.

🔍 Project Overview
The Dynamic Image Slider fetches images from an API and displays them in a sliding format. It features navigation arrows, a loading spinner, error handling, and visual indicators for easy navigation.

🌟 Features
Header Component: Simple and clean header to give context to the slider.
Image Slider Component: Fetches images from an API and displays them in a sliding format.
Navigation Arrows: Users can navigate through the images using left and right arrows.
Loading Spinner: Indicates data loading status for a smooth user experience.
Error Handling: Displays error messages if the API call fails.
Indicators: Visual indicators at the bottom allow users to jump to a specific image.
🔧 Technical Details
Frontend Technologies: ReactJS, CSS
Icons: React Icons
API Integration: Fetches images from Lorem Picsum with customizable parameters.
State Management: Manages loading, error states, and current slide using React hooks (useState, useEffect).
